<h1 class="off">A Traditional Understanding</h1><br>

Beauty seduces many to pursue healthful measures.  The quest for beauty and
longevity is universal and has prevailed throughout the ages. Preoccupation
with youth, appearance, and longevity is certainly not the exclusive domain
of citizens of the modern Western world.  Before the Warring States period
of Chinese history (475–221 BC) having acupuncture treatment for cosmetic
concerns was primarily a luxury, generally reserved for the Empress and the
imperial concubines to initiate the healing process for rejuvenation and
longevity.  Currently in China you will find an acupuncture department in
most hospitals and universities, referred to in Mandarin as mei rong. <br>
