As the partner of the lung, the large intestine also affects the skin profoundly
and thus many points on the large intestine meridian are used for affecting the
skin of the face. The stomach meridian traverses much of the face and is often
used to obtain local cosmetic effect. The stomach is the interior-exterior
partner to the spleen and accordingly these points help to tone the flesh
(the muscles and the fat underlying the skin). This communication of the lung
and the spleen (zang organs) and the stomach and the large intestine (fuorgans)
allows them to act synergistically and to substitute for each other in their
functions.<br>

